    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is doing something weird. the fan is making this loud humming sound but the blades arent actually spinning. what could be causing that and is it safe to go out there and look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming sound with no spinning blades on your AC unit is a classic sign of a mechanical issue, like a stuck motor or a capacitor problem. It's usually not immediately dangerous, but you should be cautious, especially around electrical components. It's best to turn the power off at the breaker before you even approach the unit, just to be safe. If you're not comfortable, calling a professional technician is the wisest move.",
