    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i already turned the power off at the breaker so i'm safe to look at it. i was thinking about checking the capacitor since i read online that they cause this kind of thing. how would i tell if it's actually blown or if something else is going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since you've already shut off the power, you're doing the right thing, which is commendable! A good first step is checking the capacitor, as those often fail in a way that makes the motor hum but won't spin. You can visually inspect the capacitor first; if it looks swollen, bulging, or has any signs of leaking fluid, it's likely blown. If it looks fine, you'll need a multimeter to test its capacitance value.",
